metadata.name: Stack of Shapes #3
metadata.description:
Inspired by sketches I'd draw in my college notebook during class. This piece uses a hand-drawn stroke style to draw a stack of overlapping shapes. Look closely and see that the lines are made of thousands of tiny dots. Iterations vary by color scheme, background color, line thickness, density, and more, with a small chance of using a rainbow color palette.  
  
Press R to re-run the drawing animation; enter to save the image in high quality. Enjoy!

metadata.name: Притяжение #56
metadata.description:
Inspired by Kazimir Malevich works, “Притяжение” features the connection between shapes, their positions and colours.
Although, as the work tries to develop further into a non-objective world, some real sceneries can still be associated with it.

——————

Rendering takes around 20 seconds at 60 fps, might take longer on older devices.
Press [1…6] to change an image resolution up to 10k.
Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.
